notes:
MFP.    Awarded the Victory and War Medals.    First served abroad (1) France,, 28/5/1916 to 15/8/1916.   Formerly Gnr. Royal Field Artillery. No. 127165.   Info from pension record: Born Glasgow, enlisted at Leeds, formerly Gnr. Royal Field Artillery, No.127165.   Enlisted 29/12/15, home address: 51 Coburg St, Leeds, occupation Tailor, age 22.5 years.      Sustained in action a gun shot wound to head, 21/7/1916. This man is worse and now suffers from Jacksonian epilepsy.   He should be admitted to hospital for observation and treatment, 15/1/1919.  10/12/17 discharged no longer physically fit for war service.   Served France 28/5/16 to 15/8/16.   Pension documents stamped deceased.
Info from pension index cards:- 4/MG/3250.   Goldstone, Claud, MFP, P/8710, A/L/Cpl, 10/12/17 discharged, 51 Coburg Street, Leeds.   No other details.
Claud Goldstone.;
